      "text": "Regional integration and globalization: In recent decades, South American countries have sought to integrate their economies and political systems through organizations such as the Union of South American Nations and the Mercosur trade bloc. At the same time, the region has been impacted by globalization, with foreign investment and trade reshaping the region's economies and societies.\n"
    },
